# Rules for @ConfigurationProperties

**IMPORTANT:** When creating classes with `@ConfigurationProperties`:

1. **All values are required** — must be set in `application.yml`
2. **Do not set default values in code** — only in configuration
3. **Use validation** — `@NotNull`, `@Min`, `@Max` to ensure valid values
4. **Use wrapper types** (`Integer`, `Double`, `Boolean`) to support `@NotNull`
5. **Validation ensures** all values are set and valid at application startup
6. **Configuration only in main file** — values are set ONLY in `application.yml`. In profile files (`application-local.yml`, `application-dev.yml`, `application-mock.yml`, `application-test.yml`) override only values that differ from defaults. Do not duplicate the same values into every file.

**Correct usage example:**
```java
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "open-daimon.context")
@Validated
@Getter
@Setter
public class ContextProperties {
    @NotNull(message = "maxContextTokens is required")
    @Min(value = 1000, message = "maxContextTokens must be >= 1000")
    private Integer maxContextTokens; // NO default in code!
    
    @NotNull(message = "summaryTriggerThreshold is required")
    @Min(value = 0, message = "summaryTriggerThreshold must be >= 0.0")
    @Max(value = 1, message = "summaryTriggerThreshold must be <= 1.0")
    private Double summaryTriggerThreshold; // NO default in code!
    
    // ... other fields
}
```

**WRONG:**
```java
private int maxContextTokens = 8000; // ❌ Default in code
private Integer maxContextTokens = 8000; // ❌ Default in code
```

**CORRECT:**
```java
@NotNull
@Min(value = 1000)
private Integer maxContextTokens; // ✅ Value only from application.yml
```

**Imports:**
```java
import jakarta.validation.constraints.Max;
import jakarta.validation.constraints.Min;
import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;
import org.springframework.boot.context.properties.ConfigurationProperties;
import org.springframework.validation.annotation.Validated;
```
